##

Below is the script I used at time of writing to download the log.html file from my HDHomerun Connect
The downloaded file needs be parsed to remove non-log items, and to add only the new log items to the
file monitored by Splunk.  I run this script with cron at a 5-15 minute interval

There is likely a much better way to collect this data but it is my first attempt at gathering data from an HTTP source

Please use this as a starting point for your data collection or contact me on slack @ dpotter with a better way to get the data



##


 #!/bin/bash
## This script will request the log from your HDHomerun
##      output to /var/log/hdhomerun/hdhomerun.tmp
##      This file will be processed by grepping for the actual log lines and discarding the rest
##      and output to /var/log/hdhomerun/hdhomerun.log
## Script should be run with cronjob to execute as the splunk user

### VARS ###

LOG_HOST="http://192.168.1.245"
LOG_PATH="/var/log/hdhomerun"

##* Need to add test if file exists for the first run.
cp $LOG_PATH/hdhomerun.log $LOG_PATH/hdhomerun.log.old

## download the log as hdhomerun.tmp
curl $LOG_HOST/log.html > $LOG_PATH/hdhomerun.tmp

## grep to parse the relevant log lines and save as hdhomerun.log.tmp
grep 'System:\|Tuner:\|HTTP:' $LOG_PATH/hdhomerun.tmp > $LOG_PATH/hdhomerun.log.tmp

##
diff -u $LOG_PATH/hdhomerun.log.old $LOG_PATH/hdhomerun.log.tmp |grep -E "^\+" |sed 's/+//' | sed 's/^++//' >> $LOG_PATH/hdhomerun.log

